  "root_text": {
    "snp1.10:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 1.10 ",
    "snp1.10:0.2": "Āḷavakasutta ",
    "snp1.10:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "snp1.10:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā āḷaviyaṁ viharati āḷavakassa yakkhassa bhavane. ",
    "snp1.10:1.3": "Atha kho āḷavako yakkho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "snp1.10:1.4": "“nikkhama, samaṇā”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:1.5": "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā nikkhami. ",
    "snp1.10:1.6": "“Pavisa, samaṇā”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:1.7": "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā pāvisi. ",
    "snp1.10:2.1": "Dutiyampi kho …pe… ",
    "snp1.10:2.2": "tatiyampi kho āḷavako yakkho bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "snp1.10:2.3": "“nikkhama, samaṇā”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:2.4": "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā nikkhami. ",
    "snp1.10:2.5": "“Pavisa, samaṇā”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:2.6": "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā pāvisi. ",
    "snp1.10:3.1": "Catutthampi kho āḷavako yakkho bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "snp1.10:3.2": "“nikkhama, samaṇā”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:3.3": "“Na khvāhaṁ taṁ, āvuso, nikkhamissāmi. ",
    "snp1.10:3.4": "Yaṁ te karaṇīyaṁ, taṁ karohī”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:4.1": "“Pañhaṁ taṁ, samaṇa, pucchissāmi. ",
    "snp1.10:4.2": "Sace me na byākarissasi, cittaṁ vā te khipissāmi, hadayaṁ vā te phālessāmi, pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipissāmī”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:5.1": "“Na khvāhaṁ taṁ, āvuso, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya yo me cittaṁ vā khipeyya hadayaṁ vā phāleyya pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipeyya. ",
    "snp1.10:5.2": "Api ca tvaṁ, āvuso, puccha yadākaṅkhasī”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:5.3": "Atha kho āḷavako yakkho bhagavantaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "snp1.10:6.1": "“Kiṁ sūdha vittaṁ purisassa seṭṭhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:6.2": "Kiṁ su suciṇṇaṁ sukhamāvahāti; ",
    "snp1.10:6.3": "Kiṁ su have sādutaraṁ rasānaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:6.4": "Kathaṁjīviṁ jīvitamāhu seṭṭhaṁ”. ",
    "snp1.10:7.1": "“Saddhīdha vittaṁ purisassa seṭṭhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:7.2": "Dhammo suciṇṇo sukhamāvahāti; ",
    "snp1.10:7.3": "Saccaṁ have sādutaraṁ rasānaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:7.4": "Paññājīviṁ jīvitamāhu seṭṭhaṁ”. ",
    "snp1.10:8.1": "“Kathaṁ su tarati oghaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:8.2": "kathaṁ su tarati aṇṇavaṁ; ",
    "snp1.10:8.3": "Kathaṁ su dukkhamacceti, ",
    "snp1.10:8.4": "kathaṁ su parisujjhati”. ",
    "snp1.10:9.1": "“Saddhāya tarati oghaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:9.2": "appamādena aṇṇavaṁ; ",
    "snp1.10:9.3": "Vīriyena dukkhamacceti, ",
    "snp1.10:9.4": "paññāya parisujjhati”. ",
    "snp1.10:10.1": "“Kathaṁ su labhate paññaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:10.2": "kathaṁ su vindate dhanaṁ; ",
    "snp1.10:10.3": "Kathaṁ su kittiṁ pappoti, ",
    "snp1.10:10.4": "kathaṁ mittāni ganthati; ",
    "snp1.10:10.5": "Asmā lokā paraṁ lokaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:10.6": "kathaṁ pecca na socati”. ",
    "snp1.10:11.1": "“Saddahāno arahataṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:11.2": "dhammaṁ nibbānapattiyā; ",
    "snp1.10:11.3": "Sussūsaṁ labhate paññaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:11.4": "appamatto vicakkhaṇo. ",
    "snp1.10:12.1": "Patirūpakārī dhuravā, ",
    "snp1.10:12.2": "uṭṭhātā vindate dhanaṁ; ",
    "snp1.10:12.3": "Saccena kittiṁ pappoti, ",
    "snp1.10:12.4": "dadaṁ mittāni ganthati. ",
    "snp1.10:13.1": "Yassete caturo dhammā, ",
    "snp1.10:13.2": "saddhassa gharamesino; ",
    "snp1.10:13.3": "Saccaṁ dhammo dhiti cāgo, ",
    "snp1.10:13.4": "sa ve pecca na socati. ",
    "snp1.10:14.1": "Iṅgha aññepi pucchassu, ",
    "snp1.10:14.2": "puthū samaṇabrāhmaṇe; ",
    "snp1.10:14.3": "Yadi saccā damā cāgā, ",
    "snp1.10:14.4": "khantyā bhiyyodha vijjati”. ",
    "snp1.10:15.1": "“Kathaṁ nu dāni puccheyyaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:15.2": "Puthū samaṇabrāhmaṇe; ",
    "snp1.10:15.3": "Yohaṁ ajja pajānāmi, ",
    "snp1.10:15.4": "Yo attho samparāyiko. ",
    "snp1.10:16.1": "Atthāya vata me buddho, ",
    "snp1.10:16.2": "Vāsāyāḷavimāgamā; ",
    "snp1.10:16.3": "Yohaṁ ajja pajānāmi, ",
    "snp1.10:16.4": "Yattha dinnaṁ mahapphalaṁ. ",
    "snp1.10:17.1": "So ahaṁ vicarissāmi, ",
    "snp1.10:17.2": "Gāmā gāmaṁ purā puraṁ; ",
    "snp1.10:17.3": "Namassamāno sambuddhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.10:17.4": "Dhammassa ca sudhammatan”ti. ",
    "snp1.10:17.5": "Āḷavakasuttaṁ dasamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp1.10:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 1.10 ",
    "snp1.10:0.2": "With Āḷavaka ",
    "snp1.10:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "snp1.10:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Āḷavī in the haunt of the native spirit Āḷavaka. ",
    "snp1.10:1.3": "Then the native spirit Āḷavaka went up to the Buddha, and said to him: ",
    "snp1.10:1.4": "“Get out, ascetic!” ",
    "snp1.10:1.5": "Saying, “All right, respectable sir,” the Buddha went out. ",
    "snp1.10:1.6": "“Get in, ascetic!” ",
    "snp1.10:1.7": "Saying, “All right, respectable sir,” the Buddha went in. ",
    "snp1.10:2.1": "For a second time … ",
    "snp1.10:2.2": "And for a third time the native spirit Āḷavaka said to the Buddha, ",
    "snp1.10:2.3": "“Get out, ascetic!” ",
    "snp1.10:2.4": "Saying, “All right, respectable sir,” the Buddha went out. ",
    "snp1.10:2.5": "“Get in, ascetic!” ",
    "snp1.10:2.6": "Saying, “All right, respectable sir,” the Buddha went in. ",
    "snp1.10:3.1": "And for a fourth time the native spirit Āḷavaka said to the Buddha, ",
    "snp1.10:3.2": "“Get out, ascetic!” ",
    "snp1.10:3.3": "“No, respectable sir, I won’t get out. ",
    "snp1.10:3.4": "Do what you must.” ",
    "snp1.10:4.1": "“I will ask you a question, ascetic. ",
    "snp1.10:4.2": "If you don’t answer me, I’ll drive you insane, or explode your heart, or grab you by the feet and throw you to the far shore of the Ganges!” ",
    "snp1.10:5.1": "“I don’t see anyone in this world with its gods, Māras, and Divinities, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans who could do that to me. ",
    "snp1.10:5.2": "But anyway, ask what you wish.” ",
    "snp1.10:5.3": "Then the native spirit Āḷavaka addressed the Buddha in verse: ",
    "snp1.10:6.1": "“What’s a person’s best wealth? ",
    "snp1.10:6.2": "What brings happiness when practiced well? ",
    "snp1.10:6.3": "What’s the sweetest taste of all? ",
    "snp1.10:6.4": "The one they say has the best life: how do they live?” ",
    "snp1.10:7.1": "“Faith here is a person’s best wealth. ",
    "snp1.10:7.2": "the teaching brings happiness when practiced well. ",
    "snp1.10:7.3": "Truth is the sweetest taste of all. ",
    "snp1.10:7.4": "The one they say has the best life lives by wisdom.” ",
    "snp1.10:8.1": "“How do you cross the flood? ",
    "snp1.10:8.2": "How do you cross the deluge? ",
    "snp1.10:8.3": "How do you get over suffering? ",
    "snp1.10:8.4": "How do you get purified?” ",
    "snp1.10:9.1": "“By faith you cross the flood, ",
    "snp1.10:9.2": "and by diligence the deluge. ",
    "snp1.10:9.3": "By energy you get past suffering, ",
    "snp1.10:9.4": "and you’re purified by wisdom.” ",
    "snp1.10:10.1": "“How do you get wisdom? ",
    "snp1.10:10.2": "How do you earn wealth? ",
    "snp1.10:10.3": "How do you get a good reputation? ",
    "snp1.10:10.4": "How do you hold on to friends? ",
    "snp1.10:10.5": "How do the departed not grieve ",
    "snp1.10:10.6": "when passing from this world to the next?” ",
    "snp1.10:11.1": "“One who is diligent and discerning ",
    "snp1.10:11.2": "gains wisdom by wanting to learn, ",
    "snp1.10:11.3": "having faith in the perfected ones, ",
    "snp1.10:11.4": "and the teaching for becoming extinguished. ",
    "snp1.10:12.1": "Being responsible, acting appropriately, ",
    "snp1.10:12.2": "and working hard you earn wealth. ",
    "snp1.10:12.3": "Truthfulness wins you a good reputation. ",
    "snp1.10:12.4": "You hold on to friends by giving. ",
    "snp1.10:13.1": "A faithful householder of discernment ",
    "snp1.10:13.2": "who possesses these four qualities ",
    "snp1.10:13.3": "does not grieve after passing away: ",
    "snp1.10:13.4": "truth, principle, steadfastness, and generosity. ",
    "snp1.10:14.1": "Go ahead, ask others as well, ",
    "snp1.10:14.2": "there are many ascetics and brahmins. ",
    "snp1.10:14.3": "See whether anything better is found ",
    "snp1.10:14.4": "than truth, principle, generosity, and patience.” ",
    "snp1.10:15.1": "“Why now would I question ",
    "snp1.10:15.2": "the many ascetics and brahmins? ",
    "snp1.10:15.3": "Today I understand ",
    "snp1.10:15.4": "what’s good for the next life. ",
    "snp1.10:16.1": "It was truly for my benefit ",
    "snp1.10:16.2": "that the Buddha came to stay at Āḷavī. ",
    "snp1.10:16.3": "Today I understand ",
    "snp1.10:16.4": "where a gift is very fruitful. ",
    "snp1.10:17.1": "I myself will journey ",
    "snp1.10:17.2": "village to village, town to town, ",
    "snp1.10:17.3": "paying homage to the Buddha, ",
    "snp1.10:17.4": "and the clear rightness of the teaching!” "
  },
